</section><section id="fs-id1412646">
<title>Solve Commission Applications</title>
<para id="fs-id1166497132799">Sales people often receive a <term>commission</term>, or percent of total sales, for their sales. Their income may be just the commission they earn, or it may be their commission added to their hourly wages or salary. The commission they earn is calculated as a certain percent of the price of each item they sell. That percent is called the <emphasis effect="bold">rate of commission</emphasis>.</para><note id="fs-id1536999"><title>Commission</title><para id="fs-id1166490874403">A commission is a percentage of total sales as determined by the rate of commission.</para>
<equation id="fs-id1274938" class="unnumbered"><label/><m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>commission</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>rate of commission</m:mtext><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mtext>total sales</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></equation>
</note><para id="fs-id1166497195832">To find the commission on a sale, multiply the rate of commission by the total sales. Just as we did for computing sales tax, remember to first convert the rate of commission from a percent to a decimal.</para>
<example id="fs-id1166497212472">
<exercise id="fs-id1504499"><problem id="fs-id1394280">
<para id="fs-id1166497409214">Helene is a realtor. She receives <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>3%</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> commission when she sells a house. How much commission will she receive for selling a house that costs <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>$260,000</m:mtext><m:mo>?</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1899170">
<title>Solution</title>
<table id="eip-id1168468246173" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="The figures shows the steps to solving the problem. It shows eight steps. Identify what you are asked to find: What is the commission? Choose a variable to represent it: Let the variable c be equal the commission. Write a sentence that gives the information to find it: The commission is 3% of the price. Translate into an equation: The commission is represented by c. The word 'is' is represented with an equals sign. 3% is written as 0.03. The word 'of' is represented with a multiplication dot. The price, $260,000, is written as 260,000. The equation is c = 0.03 · 260,000. Simplify: c = 7,800. Change the commission rate to percent form: r = 8.5%. Write a complete sentence that answers the question: Helene will receive a commission of $7,800. Check if this answer is reasonable: Yes. 1% of $260,000 is $2,600, and $7,800 is three times $2,600.">
<label/><tgroup cols="2">
<tbody>

<row>
<entry>Identify what you are asked to find.</entry>
<entry>What is the commission?</entry>
</row>

<row>
<entry>Choose a variable to represent it. </entry>
<entry>Let <m:math><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo></m:math> the commission.</entry>
</row>

<row> 
<entry>Write a sentence that gives the information to find it.</entry>
<entry>The commission is 3% of the price.</entry>
</row>

 <row>
   <entry>Translate into an equation.</entry>
   <entry><media id="eip-id1168468309687" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_06_03_016_img-01.png"/></media></entry>
 </row>

<row> 
<entry>Simplify.</entry>
<entry><media id="eip-id1168468328098" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_06_03_016_img-02.png"/></media></entry>
</row>

<row>
<entry>Change to percent form.</entry>
<entry><media id="eip-id1168469636787" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_06_03_016_img-03.png"/></media></entry>
</row>


 <row>
 <entry>Check. Is this answer reasonable?</entry>
<entry/>
</row>

<row>
 <entry>Yes. 1% of $260,000 is $2,600, and $7,800 is three times $2,600. </entry>
 <entry/>
</row>


 <row> 
 <entry>Write a complete sentence that answers the question.</entry>
 <entry>Helene will receive a commission of $7,800.</entry>
 </row>

</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</solution>
</exercise></example>
