<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1166482443363"><term>commission</term><meaning id="fs-id1739163">A commission is a percentage of total sales as determined by the rate of commission.</meaning></definition>

<definition id="fs-id1361485"><term>discount</term><meaning id="fs-id1387176">An amount of discount is a percent off the original price, determined by the discount rate.</meaning></definition>

<definition id="fs-id1468532"><term>mark-up</term><meaning id="fs-id1166490904624">The mark-up is the amount added to the wholesale price, determined by the mark-up rate.</meaning></definition>

<definition id="fs-id1105267"><term>sales tax</term><meaning id="fs-id1339010">The sales tax is a percent of the purchase price.                        </meaning></definition>


</glossary>
